abstractText: Individual and average water hardened green egg weights are used to generate green egg fecundity values for fish spawned at the hatchery and in the predictive fecundity regression equations used to generate estimates of potential egg deposition for adults that spawned in spawning channels. See Reintroduction of Lower Columbia River Chum Salmon into Duncan Creek FFY 2008 to 2010 Summary Report for more https://pisces.bpa.gov/release/documents/documentviewer.aspx?doc=P123791
title: Weights: water hardened green egg v1.0
